<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="habit and habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Habit and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Solitary to scattered on dead wood debris of conifers, in summer.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">The Republic of Korea</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis clavicystidiata" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="clavicystidiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis clavicystidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. omphalodes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="omphalodes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">G. omphalodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. menehune" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="menehune">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. menehune</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Kim &amp; Cho &amp; Park &amp; Park &amp; Kim &amp; Kim &amp; Lim" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis omphalodes" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="omphalodes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis omphalodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in their larger pileus (2-30 mm), a darker colored stipe, smaller basidiospores (5-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), and thinner hyphae in the pileipellis (5-8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R.H.Petersen" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Desjardin, Halling &amp; Hemmes" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis menehune" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="menehune">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis menehune</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. clavicystidiata" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="clavicystidiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. clavicystidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its larger pileus (8-30 mm), buff lamellae, longer stipe (15-60 mm), longer basidiospores (7.5-9.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-4.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, Q = 2.2), and longer caulocystidia (16-67 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" author="Desjardin, DE" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="166 - 176" refId="B10" refString="Desjardin, DE, Halling, RE, Hemmes, DE, 1999. Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus. Mycologia 91 (1): 166 - 176, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" title="Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" volume="91" year="1999">Desjardin et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. clavicystidiata" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="clavicystidiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. clavicystidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is phylogenetically close to 
<taxonomicName genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. pseudomphalodes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="pseudomphalodes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. pseudomphalodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Kim &amp; Cho &amp; Park &amp; Park &amp; Kim &amp; Kim &amp; Lim" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis pseudomphalodes" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pseudomphalodes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis pseudomphalodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has relatively few references for comparison, but differences can be found in the lengths of the stipe (3-4 mm) and cheilocystidia (40 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) when compared with 
<taxonomicName genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. clavicystidiata" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="clavicystidiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. clavicystidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" author="Dennis, R" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the British Mycological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B8" refString="Dennis, R, 1961. Fungi venezuelani: IV. Agaricales. Kew Bulletin 15(1): 67-156[+ii]. https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" title="Fungi venezuelani: IV. Agaricales. Kew Bulletin 15 (1): 67 - 156 [+ ii]." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" year="1961">Dennis 1961</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
